  "prompt": "What is the best gaming PC I can get for 1400\u20ac?",
  "response": "Building or buying a gaming PC for \u20ac1400 can get you a very capable machine that can handle modern games at 1080p or 1440p with high to ultra settings. Here\u2019s a balanced configuration you can consider:\n\n---\n\n### **Recommended Build (\u20ac1400)**  \n#### **CPU**: AMD Ryzen 5 7600  \n- Great for gaming and multitasking, with excellent single-core performance and PCIe 5.0 support.  \n- Price: ~\u20ac230  \n\n#### **GPU**: NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4060 Ti (8GB)  \n- Solid for 1080p and 1440p gaming with ray tracing and DLSS support.  \n- Price: ~\u20ac450  \n\n#### **Motherboard**: MSI B650M PRO-VDH WiFi  \n- Compatible with Ryzen 7000 series, supports DDR5, and includes WiFi.  \n- Price: ~\u20ac160  \n\n#### **RAM**: 16GB (2x8GB) DDR5-6000  \n- Fast memory for gaming and multitasking.  \n- Price: ~\u20ac100  \n\n#### **Storage**: 1TB NVMe SSD (e.g., Samsung 980 or WD Black SN770)  \n- Fast storage for quick boot times and game loading.  \n- Price: ~\u20ac60  \n\n#### **Power Supply**: Corsair CX650M (650W, 80+ Bronze)  \n- Reliable and efficient PSU for this build.  \n- Price: ~\u20ac80  \n\n#### **Case**: NZXT H5 Flow  \n- Good airflow and cable management.  \n- Price: ~\u20ac90  \n\n#### **Cooling**: AMD Wraith Prism (included with CPU) or a budget air cooler like the Cooler Master Hyper 212  \n- Price: ~\u20ac30  \n\n#### **Total**: ~\u20ac1400  \n\n---\n\n### **Prebuilt Option**  \nIf you prefer a prebuilt PC, look for systems with similar specs (e.g., Ryzen 5 7600 or Intel i5-13600K paired with RTX 4060 Ti or RX 7700 XT). Brands like Acer, HP OMEN, or custom builders like NZXT or CyberPowerPC often have good options in this price range.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips**:  \n1. **Future Upgrades**: This build leaves room for upgrades like more RAM, a better GPU, or additional storage.  \n2. **Sales**: Check for discounts or bundle deals on sites like Amazon, Newegg, or local retailers.  \n3. **RTX vs AMD GPUs**: If ray tracing isn\u2019t a priority, you could opt for an AMD RX 7700 XT for better raw performance in some games.  \n\nThis setup will handle most modern AAA titles at high settings while staying within your budget.",
